This paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of structured output support vector machines (SVMs) for discriminative segmentation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of optimization algorithms, which could fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
